---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Wammy's House Squad, its writing ethos, and contact details."
  currentPath="/about"
>
  <section class="panel page-intro">
    <h2>About Wammy's House Squad</h2>
    <p class="page-intro__lead">
      Wammy&apos;s House Squad is a writing circle made up of White Hat School alumni,
      gathered around L as mentor and fellow explorer. We study the world of games in
      our own way, moving between technical analysis and the lived perspective of players,
      then turn those observations into a shared public archive.
    </p>
    <p class="page-intro__lead">
      The articles collected here may take the form of reviews, technical notes,
      reverse engineering logs, recommendations, or quiet field records. Everything is
      published for personal study and analysis, grounded in ethical practice and respect
      for copyright. Our purpose is simple: to explore the world of games through our own
      lens, and to believe that small, careful records can eventually contribute to a
      wider change.
    </p>
    <p class="page-intro__local" lang="ko">
      와미즈 하우스 스쿼드는 전원 화이트햇스쿨 출신으로 이루어진 모임으로,
      멘토인 엘과 함께 게임 세상을 우리만의 방식으로 분석하고 탐구합니다.
      우리는 플레이어의 감각과 기술적인 시선을 오가며 얻은 관찰과 기록을
      하나의 아카이브로 차곡차곡 쌓아 갑니다.
    </p>
    <p class="page-intro__local" lang="ko">
      이곳에 올라오는 모든 글은 개인적인 연구와 분석을 위한 기록이며,
      저작권법을 준수하고 윤리적 기술자로서의 태도를 잊지 않으려 합니다.
      우리의 목적은 단 하나, 게임을 좋아하는 사람들이 우리만의 관점으로
      게임 세상을 더 깊이 탐구해 나가는 것입니다. 우리는 ethical hacker로서
      배우고 익히며, 작은 경험과 기록이 모여 결국 더 나은 변화를 만드는 데
      기여할 수 있다고 믿습니다.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="panel">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2>Principles</h2>
      <p>The squad writes with curiosity, discipline, and responsibility.</p>
    </div>
    <ul class="template-list">
      <li>We approach games from both technical and player-centered perspectives.</li>
      <li>All articles are written for personal research, study, and responsible discussion.</li>
      <li>We aim to respect copyright, preserve context, and keep an ethics-first mindset.</li>
      <li>Small observations matter; careful notes can become meaningful knowledge over time.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="panel">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>If you find a problem with an article or need to reach the person in charge, use the address below.</p>
    </div>
    <p class="page-intro__local">
      Responsible contact: <a href="mailto:moonhug@icloud.com">moonhug@icloud.com</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
